title: Introduction to Statistical Learning
description: From their website --> This book provides an introduction to statistical learning methods.    It is aimed for upper level undergraduate students, masters students and Ph.D.    students in the non-mathematical sciences. The book also contains a number of R  labs with detailed explanations on how to implement the various methods in real   life settings, and should be a valuable resource for a practicing data scientist.

It also covers logic and reasoning at a level suitable   for a general education course.
